column1: 1895 gauge must have moved as elevation decreases to 117 ft but no details of move
This MS&L Railway Company site is part of its Sheffield and South Yorkshire Navigation system of canals and waterways, which came under MS&LR control in 1864.
MS&LR were forced to divest these canals and waterways in 1895.
MS&LR owned the Sheffield and Tinsley Canal on which Tinsley Locks are situated.
The lower locks are a good match for the 143 ft elevation given on the early rainfall sheets.

The change of elevation to 117 ft in 1895 corresponds with MS&LR selling the Sheffield and Tinsley Canal, and may indicate a move of the gauge to a nearby railway location, perhaps to Tinsley Station (SK397908) which is at about the right elevation.
